task_description: Facing the building to your South (approx. 187°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: Moving to the right (node 1) will give me a different perspective of the main building, allowing me to potentially see its full height from ground to roof more clearly.
Moving back (move 2) will return me to my previous position where I was facing the main building to the South, allowing me to view it directly for height estimation.
After multiple attempts to rotate south to view the main building, I'll estimate its height as 18 meters, assuming it's a 6-story structure with each floor approximately 3 meters tall.
